From 48056f9822b0826ec3aef1c5f139e81beec487d7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Narendhar Reddy <quic_nare@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Feb 2025 10:26:38 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PLATFORM ath12k: Add support for collecting PHY logs along with QDSS
Introduce changes to the ath12k driver to enable
the collection of PHY logs along with QDSS. Update
the driver to handle additional arguments for PHY log
collection in the same QDSS sys debug file.

In case of split phy, two phy bins will be collected.
This bins are needed for the ADC validation.

Add new QMI structures and functions to manage QDSS trace
data requests and responses.

  HOST ----(QMI_WLANFW_QDSS_TRACE_OFF_V01)   --------> FW
  HOST <----(QMI_EVENT_QDSS_TRACE_REQ_DATA(QDSS)) ---- FW
  HOST <----(QMI_EVENT_QDSS_TRACE_REQ_DATA(PHY)) ----- FW
  HOST ----(QMI_WLFW_QDSS_TRACE_DATA_REQ_V01) -------> FW

Commands to get phy logs:
 QDSS:  echo 0 > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/<chip_name>/trace_qdss
 PHYA0: echo 0 0x40 > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/<chip_name>/trace_qdss
 PHYA1: echo 0 0x80 > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/<chip_name>/trace_qdss

Signed-off-by: Narendhar Reddy <quic_nare@quicinc.com>
